Could it be because he wasn't paying enough attention to her when she told the other guy that her boyfriend didn't notice or tell her about her new hairstyle? Is it because he forgot his anniversary? Is it because he is bad at sex but he thinks nothing is wrong? It will be because even though he knew that his girlfriend stopped seeing her lover, he normalized the situation and made sure that nothing ever happened here, but he continued to sucks at sex even though he had a trauma and never asked for professional help or at least discuss it with the person involved?

Rather, they are feeling empathy for an MC, who in the 2 episodes did absolutely nothing, only crying for his own cowardice and jerking off in the bathroom.

To finish, I don't care about this fetish story, I don't feel any empathy for any character.

@tatsuya790 I just try to say that even though the 2 characters are guilty (MC is a coward and the FMC is a pushover) people in the comments prefer to justify the MC just because he is the only one who is having a bad time, even though he himself created the problem indirectly and does not have the balls to confront it.

Self-insertion in this type of character is not healthy. Have a nice day you too.

That's a half truth.

